Now I can look like an idiot
while I freeze to death.

37
00:02:22,059 --> 00:02:24,186
-[Howling stops]
- Woof.

38
00:02:24,269 --> 00:02:27,397
Actually, these sacks
are really working a treat.

39
00:02:27,439 --> 00:02:29,941
I'm sweating like
an everyday Susan in here.

40
00:02:31,068 --> 00:02:32,694
Oh, I see.

41
00:02:33,445 --> 00:02:35,197
That works, too.

42
00:02:38,909 --> 00:02:40,327
What the...

43
00:02:51,713 --> 00:02:52,964
Neat.

44
00:02:53,048 --> 00:02:56,218
It's like the border to
the Ice Kingdom but not really.

45
00:02:56,301 --> 00:02:58,845
[Wind howls]

46
00:02:58,929 --> 00:03:01,223
Tush!
Coming down hard again.

47
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:03,100
I better head back.

48
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:04,601
[Wind howling,
electricity buzzes]

49
00:03:04,601 --> 00:03:05,727
Shack?

50
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:07,437
Shack.

51
00:03:07,479 --> 00:03:08,730
Sack?

52
00:03:08,814 --> 00:03:09,940
Shack!

53
00:03:09,981 --> 00:03:12,818
Ow! Oof!
Oh! Oh! Aah! Ohh!

54
00:03:14,569 --> 00:03:15,862
[Thud!]

55
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:18,490
Ohh.

56
00:03:19,449 --> 00:03:22,077
[Birds chirping]

57
00:03:25,205 --> 00:03:26,331
[Animal squeaking]

58
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:28,333
Ruh-roh.

59
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:30,627
Looks like someone's
still living here.

60
00:03:30,711 --> 00:03:32,003
[Chuckles]

61
00:03:32,087 --> 00:03:33,880
Look at you.
You're thick as heck.

62
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:35,507
You're thicker
than a normal Susan.

63
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:36,383
Whoa!

64
00:03:37,509 --> 00:03:39,970
Good grief, man!
Were you in on this?!

65
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:41,388
That's shady.

66
00:03:41,471 --> 00:03:43,598
Do your parents know
what you do all day?

67
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:45,016
I mean, honestly.

68
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:46,017
[Leaves rustle]

69
00:03:46,101 --> 00:03:47,394
[Heavy footsteps]

70
00:03:49,271 --> 00:03:51,398
Giant bear?
Come on!

71
00:03:51,523 --> 00:03:54,025
I fought The Lich at the edge
of space-time, man.

72
00:03:54,109 --> 00:03:57,028
You're out of your depth.
You best just roll on, brah.

73
00:03:57,028 --> 00:03:58,363
[Sniffs]

74
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:00,907
- Heyl
-[Growls]

75
00:04:00,907 --> 00:04:02,909
Hey. Hey, hey, hey, hey!

76
00:04:03,785 --> 00:04:05,746
[Growls]

77
00:04:05,787 --> 00:04:06,872
[Grunts]

78
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:07,789
[Groans]

79
00:04:07,914 --> 00:04:09,541
See?!
I told you!

80
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:11,001
ALVA:
Stop! Nej, nej, nej!

81
00:04:11,042 --> 00:04:13,545
[Speaking Swedish]

82
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:16,173
Bzzt!

83
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:18,008
[Buzzer]

84
00:04:18,008 --> 00:04:18,842
FINN: Oof!

85
00:04:18,884 --> 00:04:21,595
[Speaking Swedish]

86
00:04:26,641 --> 00:04:28,101
Come, Albert.

87
00:04:33,148 --> 00:04:35,650
[Water trickling]

88
00:04:35,776 --> 00:04:37,527
Hmm.

89
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:43,241
FINN: Hey!

90
00:04:43,283 --> 00:04:44,910
You're a human, right?

91
00:04:45,035 --> 00:04:46,661
Do you know
where my friends are?

92
00:04:46,787 --> 00:04:50,540
A dog, a robot,
and another human who smells --

93
00:04:50,624 --> 00:04:53,126
and I've been saying this
a lot -- not great.

94
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:56,671
Does this mean I made it
to the human place?

95
00:04:56,671 --> 00:04:58,048
-[Egg Whistling]
- Did you send for me?

96
00:04:58,173 --> 00:05:01,301
Are you the mayor of here
or like the tribe leader?

97
00:05:01,384 --> 00:05:03,053
I-I mean -- Agh.

98
00:05:03,053 --> 00:05:04,805
I'm sorry.
I don't know what I'm saying.

99
00:05:04,888 --> 00:05:06,807
[Whistling continues]

100
00:05:06,890 --> 00:05:08,183
Hi.

101
00:05:09,768 --> 00:05:11,520
Hmm.

102
00:05:12,938 --> 00:05:13,522
Bzzt.

103
00:05:13,563 --> 00:05:14,815
[Buzzer]

104
00:05:19,194 --> 00:05:21,446
[Whistling continues]

105
00:05:23,824 --> 00:05:25,283
Thanks.

106
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:27,828
Can I have
my backpack back...pack?

107
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:31,081
Huh?!

108
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:32,082
[Growling]

109
00:05:32,165 --> 00:05:33,208
[Clicks tongue]

110
00:05:36,336 --> 00:05:37,045
[Grunts]

111
00:05:38,213 --> 00:05:39,714
Lady!

112
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:46,596
[Growls]

113
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,348
Lady, you can't just --

114
00:05:48,431 --> 00:05:50,225
- Hmm...
- FINN: Oh!

115
00:05:52,727 --> 00:05:55,856
[Yawns]

116
00:05:55,856 --> 00:05:57,482
[Smacks lips]

117
00:06:01,319 --> 00:06:02,362
(\\[o

118
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:05,699
No!

119
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,577
(\\[o

120
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:12,497
(\\[o

121
00:06:12,581 --> 00:06:15,333
One last time, have you seen
my brother anywhere?

122
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:16,459
He looks like this.

123
00:06:22,382 --> 00:06:24,509
This guy.
His name is Jake.

124
00:06:24,634 --> 00:06:26,845
En hund!

125
00:06:26,887 --> 00:06:28,346
Mnh.

126
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:30,015
Oh.

127
00:06:33,768 --> 00:06:34,853
What?

128
00:06:38,273 --> 00:06:40,901
You want me to draw you?

129
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:42,027
Oh.

130
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:43,862
I didn't draw
that picture of Jake.

131
00:06:43,904 --> 00:06:45,363
I don't know how to draw,
really.

132
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:47,657
Banana Guard 16
tried to teach me once,

133
00:06:47,741 --> 00:06:49,034
but it didn't stick.

134
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:51,870
[Chuckles]
Okay.

135
00:06:51,912 --> 00:06:54,164
[scribbling]

136
00:06:55,415 --> 00:06:57,417
Okay.

137
00:06:59,502 --> 00:07:01,171
[Sighs]

138
00:07:01,296 --> 00:07:04,299
[Speaking Swedish]

139
00:07:07,135 --> 00:07:08,762
-[Thunder crashes]
- Oh!

140
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:17,020
[Wind howling]

141
00:07:17,062 --> 00:07:18,271
Ooh! Ooh-ooh.
Ooh. Ooh!

142
00:07:18,313 --> 00:07:19,898
Het, het, het, het, het!

143
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:21,942
Het! Het, het, het!

144
00:07:25,946 --> 00:07:28,281
What, a-are you folks afraid
of thunder?

145
00:07:31,660 --> 00:07:32,827
[Screams]

146
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:35,288
Lady! I know a lot
about living in trees,

147
00:07:35,330 --> 00:07:38,291
and this thing's not going to...
hold.

148
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:41,586
[Beep]

149
00:07:46,675 --> 00:07:48,593
This place is teched out.

150
00:07:49,552 --> 00:07:51,304
I should have known, I guess,

151
00:07:51,346 --> 00:07:53,098
since you talked
to that net earlier.

152
00:07:55,850 --> 00:07:58,061
You can't understand me,
can you?

153
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:02,440
Somethings been bubbling up
inside me.

154
00:08:02,482 --> 00:08:03,692
I really want to say it
out loud,

155
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:05,485
but I've been embarrassed.

156
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:06,987
Okay.

157
00:08:06,987 --> 00:08:08,989
Are crabs robots?

158
00:08:08,989 --> 00:08:11,116
In what way
isn't a crab a robot?

159
00:08:11,199 --> 00:08:13,868
I guess I understand
that BMO's not a crab,

160
00:08:13,952 --> 00:08:16,997
but I don't understand
why BMO's not a crab.

161
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,331
Shh!

162
00:08:22,627 --> 00:08:24,629
Lady, where did everyone go to?

163
00:08:24,713 --> 00:08:25,755
Shh.

164
00:08:36,558 --> 00:08:40,061
FINN: Hey, that's you!
Your name's Alva.

165
00:08:40,061 --> 00:08:41,021
Hi, Alva.

166
00:08:47,902 --> 00:08:49,779
Oh.

167
00:08:57,662 --> 00:08:59,456
So that's it?

168
00:08:59,539 --> 00:09:00,957
That's humans?!

169
00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:03,543
We came all this way.
[Sighs]

170
00:09:03,585 --> 00:09:05,670
It's just you and me, Alva.

171
00:09:05,712 --> 00:09:08,298
And Susan, I guess,
if she's okay.

172
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:09,466
I don't know.

173
00:09:09,591 --> 00:09:11,843
-[Howlin
g stops
- Huh? Pel

174
00:09:13,303 --> 00:09:14,596
Hmm?

175
00:09:14,721 --> 00:09:16,598
Sounds like the storm stopped.

176
00:09:18,058 --> 00:09:19,476
[Objects rattle]

177
00:09:19,601 --> 00:09:21,102
Hunden!

178
00:09:24,481 --> 00:09:26,858
Hmm.
No sign of him.

179
00:09:27,442 --> 00:09:28,985
BELGEECEIS

180
00:09:29,069 --> 00:09:29,861
Jake!

181
00:09:29,944 --> 00:09:31,362
Hyah!

182
00:09:32,197 --> 00:09:33,698
[Electricity buzzes]

183
00:09:36,117 --> 00:09:37,869
[Grunting]

184
00:09:37,869 --> 00:09:40,497
FINN: Jake!
Hey, Jake!

185
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:41,998
Oh, hey, buddy.

186
00:09:42,082 --> 00:09:44,876
Man, am I glad to see you.
Hold on a second.

187
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:46,086
[Grunts]

188
00:09:47,212 --> 00:09:48,630
Man, this place sucks!

189
00:09:48,630 --> 00:09:52,217
I got attacked by 19 giant crabs
in just the last 30 seconds.

190
00:09:52,258 --> 00:09:54,511
Yeah, man.
I almost got eaten by this --

191
00:09:54,511 --> 00:09:55,512
Hey, that's awesome.

192
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:56,763
Now let's get
the heck outta here.

193
00:09:56,846 --> 00:09:59,599
Are they coming, too?
I'm not sharing my rations.

194
00:09:59,641 --> 00:10:01,601
What?
No, this is Alva.

195
00:10:01,643 --> 00:10:03,895
I-I think she's human.

196
00:10:03,895 --> 00:10:05,105
Alva?

197
00:10:05,146 --> 00:10:06,898
Have you seen my friends?

198
00:10:06,981 --> 00:10:09,526
BMO and Susan?

199
00:10:14,114 --> 00:10:16,783
JAKE: Oh, stuff, man.
That's the slow shake.

200
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:19,160
That's the universal
death gesture!

201
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:21,287
ALVA: Nej, nej!
[Speaking Swedish]

202
00:10:32,257 --> 00:10:34,425
Oh, shoot, man.
More islands.

203
00:10:34,509 --> 00:10:37,679
BMO and Susan must've washed
all up on one of all up of them.

204
00:10:37,804 --> 00:10:40,140
Well, it looks like
there's only three more.

205
00:10:40,181 --> 00:10:41,808
This shouldn't be too hard.

206
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:44,394
Right?

207
00:10:46,271 --> 00:10:47,397
WAITER:
Sir BMO?

208
00:10:47,438 --> 00:10:48,773
[Classy piano music plays]

209
00:10:48,815 --> 00:10:50,441
Another Finn cake, sir?

210
00:10:50,567 --> 00:10:51,568
Oui.

211
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:56,781
Ah, this is the life.

212
00:10:56,823 --> 00:11:00,910
I wish you guys could be here,
too, on the moon.

213
00:11:00,952 --> 00:11:02,829
And Susan, too, I guess.

214
00:11:02,912 --> 00:11:05,081
She seems...fine.

215
00:11:18,803 --> 00:11:20,847
This party is so crazy!

